The paper deals with open-domain question answering, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also involves the use of machine learning models, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with knowledge graphs and taxonomies, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
